snippet: ['*...Midway Airport reached 109\xa0°F (43\xa0°C) one day prior and recorded a heat index of 125\xa0°F (52\xa0°C) during the 1995 heatwave....', '...The term "midway" for a fair or carnival referred originally to the Midway Plaisance, a strip of park land that still runs through the University of Chicago campus and connects the Washington and Jackson Parks....', '...The two parks themselves are connected by a wide strip of parkland called the Midway Plaisance, running adjacent to the University of Chicago....', '*...The Chicago Transit Authority (CTA) handles public transportation in the City of Chicago and a few adjacent suburbs outside of the Chicago city limits.
